Gravity

Type Category PP Power Accuracy Priority Description
5 - 6 — — 0 Enables Flying-type and Levitating Pokémon to be hit by Ground-type moves.

Effect

Lowers evasion for all.

Unaffected Moves

The following moves cannot be used while Gravity is active.

Name Type Category PP Power Accuracy Description
Bounce 5 85 85 The user bounces up, then drops on the target on the second turn. This may also paralyze it.
Floaty Fall 15 90 95 Floats in air and dives at angle. May cause flinching.
Fly 15 90 95 The user flies up into the sky and then strikes its target on the next turn.
Flying Press 10 100 95 The user dives down from the sky. This move is Fighting and Flying type simultaneously.
High Jump Kick 10 130 90 The target is hit with a knee kick from a jump. If it misses, the user is hurt instead.
Jump Kick 10 100 95 The user jumps up high, then strikes with a kick. If the kick misses, the user hurts itself.
Magnet Rise 10 — — The user levitates using electrically generated magnetism for five turns.
Sky Drop 10 60 100 The user takes the target into the sky, then drops it during the next turn.
Splash 40 — — The user just flops and splashes around to no effect at all…
Telekinesis 15 — — The user makes the target float with its psychic power, making it easier to hit for three turns.
